    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545"> 
      <head altrender="organization" id="a2">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head> 
      <p>The Prisoner Express program, sponsored by the Durland Alternatives
        Library at Cornell University, promotes rehabilitation by offering inmates
        information, education and the opportunity for creative self-expression in a
        public forum.</p> 
    </bioghist> 
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520"> 
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head> 
      <p>Art work and letters sent to the Prisoner Express program from people
        in prison in the United States, Prisoner Express newsletters and outreach
        materials, ads and material related to an exhibition of the art at Cornell in
        November 2006. The artwork includes colored pencil, crayon, and ink on paper,
        fabric, envelopes, and illustration board, plus origami.</p> 
    </scopecontent> 
